<p>The <code>dir</code> tag provides simple directory listing.</p>

<h2>Basic Directory</h2>
<pre>{open}dir 'fragments/claude/tags'{close}
  {open}$dir{close}
{open}/dir{close}</pre>
<p>Directory contents (first 10):</p>
<ul>
{dir 'fragments/claude/tags', rows=10}
  <li>{$dir}</li>
{/dir}
</ul>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The <code>dir</code> tag is simpler than <code>files</code> - it just lists entries without filtering options.</p>
<p>Use <code>files</code> for more control over filtering and file properties.</p>
